external_knowledge:
- Churn probability refers to the likelihood of a customer stopping their subscription or service with a company; 
- A higher churn probability indicates a higher likelihood of churning; 
- The churn prediction data is used to identify customers who are at risk of churning, allowing the company to take proactive measures to retain them.

sql:
SELECT AVG(churn_probability) AS average_churn_probability
FROM customer_churn
WHERE churn_reason IS NOT NULL;

SELECT churn_probability
FROM customer_churn
WHERE customer_id = 1;

SELECT credit_score_group
FROM customer_credit_score_groups
